We've test-driven a lot of lunch boxes around here. Some didn't last more than a day (cute but impossible to open!). Others have been in the rotation for years. I narrowed it down to our four very favorites in a new blog post. Like this one that's simple and affordable (and you can cram way more food into it than you think!). And even one that my teens will STILL take to school. Check out all four by tapping the link in my bio. What's YOUR favorite lunch box for yourself or your kids?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Sally/Real Mom Nutrition on June 04, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
I felt emotional about finishing this 16 ounce bottle of vanilla extract last weekend. It’s a bottle my friend bought for me at Costco last year when quarantine began and life turned upside down. I remember the kindness of her getting this for me when I couldn’t find it at my grocery store. And I remember all the baked goods I made with this vanilla that comforted us during a scary and uncertain time, when eating a slice of cake and watching Netflix was the escape we all craved after dinner, when a batch of chocolate chip cookie bars made everyone’s hard day of online school a little sweeter. I baked a lot this past year-plus. We ate a lot of homemade cakes, cookies, pies, and bread this past year-plus. And I gained a few extra pounds this past year-plus. But it was all worth it. It helped get us through. So thank you, giant bottle of vanilla. You served us well. ❤️
.
.
#pandemicbaking #costco

node.text:
I have a terrible digestive reaction to coconut oil. I accidentally got a bunch of it in a meal from a restaurant on Monday and had hours of unpleasantness yesterday and into today. Am I telling YOU to avoid coconut oil? No. This is my experience. I don't assume it's yours. Please be wary of people who tell you to avoid otherwise nourishing foods or groups of foods because those foods make THEM bloated, give THEM headaches, or make THEM fuzzy-headed. Pay attention to how foods make you feel and avoid ones that make you feel bad (like me + coconut oil). But don't feel like you need to give up certain foods (especially foods you love) just because someone else did.
.
.
#themoreyouknow🌈 #rdn #foodnotfear
